    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2004-04-29</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2004-08-10T19:44:19Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Fair Minimum Wage Act of 2004 - Amends the Fair Labor Standards Act of 1938 to increase the Federal minimum wage to: (1) $5.85 an hour, beginning on the 60th day after enactment of this Act; (2) $6.45 an hour, beginning 12 months after that 60th day; and (3) $7.00 an hour, beginning 24 months after that 60th day.</p> <p>Makes Federal minimum wage requirements applicable to the Commonwealth of the Northern Mariana Islands. Sets forth a transition period during which a specified minimum wage there shall be gradually increased to equal the Federal minimum wage. </p> <p>.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
